Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Blend sugar and butter or margarine until fluffy. Add egg. Add melted chocolate and sour cream. Blend until creamy. Sift baking soda into flour. Slowly add flour to cream mixture. Add nuts. Drop on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes. Allow to cool for a couple of minutes before removing from the cookie sheet to a wire rack.